shared_text:
Delaware Music Boosters
August 23 at 9:06 PM ·

Come join us for the Music with the Stars Virtual Event. Consider ordering carry out from one of Delaware's restaurants while you enjoy the show. Wait until you see these amazing performances showcasing the talent from right here in Delaware, Ohio!

- In lieu of a ticket this year, we are asking for a $40 donation to view the virtual event.

- We know that this has been a tough year, but we hope that you will add a donation as well.

- We will send a link and password to the email address used in the purchase shortly before the event begins streaming. The funds from the ticket sales and all donations will be used for the Delaware City Schools Choirs and Orchestras.

PLEASE SHARE!

post_text: Delaware City Schools will hold a special board meeting on Monday, August 10 at 6pm to further discuss reopening plans and safety protocols. The Delaware General Health District Commissioner will join the conversation. In order to make the meeting available to the public, the meeting will be broadcast on Facebook Live on the DCS Facebook page. The DCS Board of Education offers public participation as part of its traditional meetings. The Board will receive public participation via email at WeAreListening@delawarecityschools.net. Comments received to that email address by 2:00pm on Monday, Aug. 10, will be read during the meeting. Comments are limited to 1000 words and must include the name and address of the person submitting public participation. It is not a question and answer meeting. The board or designee will respond to any questions at a later time.

post_text:
Delaware City Schools Board Meeting (Virtual)
Monday, May 4 at 6pm

Delaware City Schools will hold a virtual board meeting on Monday, May 4 at 6pm to conduct essential business. In order to make the meeting available to the public, the meeting will be broadcast on Facebook Live on this Facebook page. The DCS Board of Education offers public participation as part of its traditional meetings. The Board will receive public participation via email at WeAreListening@delawarecityschools.net. Comments received to that email address by 2:00pm on Monday, May 4 will be read during the meeting. Comments are limited to 1000 words. It is not a question and answer meeting. The board or designee will respond to any questions at a later time. As always, if you have any questions, please reach out to us.

post_text: What an incredible gesture to support our Delaware community by Delaware Bible Church. Pick up is tomorrow 4/25.
shared_text:
Delaware Bible Church is at Delaware Bible Church.
April 23 at 4:32 PM · Delaware, OH ·

We’re thankful for a great group of volunteers who packed 515 Blessing Bags to share with our community this week. Anyone can come to our church parking lot on Saturday from 9 a.m. - 12 p.m. to pick up a free bag. All bags include helpful supplies such as hand sanitizer, toilet paper, paper towels, disinfectant wipes, a mask, and other household cleaners and supplies. We’re taking all reasonable precautions to make sure we prevent the spread of COVID-19 by isolating all of the items for 72 hours and all volunteers giving the items to those from our community will be wearing masks and gloves.

Beginning on Monday, April 6, we will offer grab -n- go lunches from 3 locations (Conger, Woodward & Willis) for curbside pickup. Visit our website for additional details as well as information on other agencies who are providing community resources. Stay well Pacers! https://www.dcs.k12.oh.us/Page/5772

post_text: We appreciate the partnership with our City!
shared_text:
City of Delaware, Ohio - Government
March 23 at 10:53 AM ·

We were “together apart” with our Delaware City Schools partners this morning. We gave the district 25 recycling bins to use with their school meals program and DCS is giving our Police Department goggles, disinfectant wipes and hand sanitizer. The hard, plastic bins work well for holding packaged lunches because they can be sanitized before and after every use and re-used. Two dedicated community partners working together but apart!

post_text: Our Family Resource Center remains available to help families during this time!
shared_text:
Family Resource Center, Delaware City Schools
March 13 at 4:43 PM ·

In light of the recent announcement about school closures, we want to assure everyone that the Family Resource Center will continue to serve our community in this time of need.

Our building will be closed to the public starting Monday 03/16, but we are ready to assist you via phone. If you are in need, please call 740-833-1619 between 9am and 2pm.

Though we will not be offering any walk-in services, we are still prepared to provide both food and diapers. Call ahead and schedule a time to pick up pre-packaged items.

If you are interested in donating food, please reach out via the phone number listed above.

Thank you for your understanding as we adjust our procedures to reflect these public health concerns. We are so grateful and proud to live in a town with such a deep conviction for community care.

post_text: We are incredibly grateful for the expertise and partnership with Delaware PD.
shared_text:
Delaware, Ohio Police Department
February 27 at 3:09 PM ·

Sharing Ideas and Knowledge to Keep Kids Safe in the City of Delaware, Ohio - Government and throughout the State. SRO. John Hartman and Chief Pijanowski were recognized yesterday by Ohio Attorney General Dave Yost for their work related to his new school safety initiatives.

"Chief Pijanowski and the Delaware Police contributed their expertise to help my office develop threat assessment training materials," said AG Yost "They're ahead of the curve in implementing these protocols, yet continue to review others' best-practices. That's the strength of this program: sharing information to help prevent violence, rather than just reacting to stop it once it's already happening."

To learn more about this initiative, check out: www.ohioattorneygeneral.gov/threatassessment

Delaware City Schools

post_text:
We're so pleased to partner with the Delaware community to be part of the Thanksgiving meals give-away. If you need a helping hand this Holiday season, you can pick up a full meal on Tuesday, Nov. 26 from 10:45-12:00 at Hayes High School.

We are also accepting $5 donations to sponsor a turkey or pie. Checks, cash or Kroger/Meijer gift cards will be accepted at Hayes High School or Willis Education Center through Friday.
shared_text:
Susie Schaffner Backus is with Ted Backus and 4 others.
November 17, 2019 at 10:10 AM ·

Hayes High School, Delaware County Juvenile and Probate Courts and the Delaware County Board of Developmental Disabilities have once again partnered to present the 5th annual “Fight Against Hunger Games”. Our goal is to provide over 225 complete Thanksgiving meal kits to those who may need help this Thanksgiving as well as stock the Pacer Pantry with non-perishable food items to be able to assist those facing food insecurity. This year all of Delaware City Schools as well as many Delaware County agencies are supporting our efforts as well with generous food donations. Please share with anyone who may need help. If you would like to help, I am still collecting $5 donations to sponsor a turkey or pie. Checks made payable to Delaware City Schools, Cash or Meijer, Walmart and Kroger gift cards are accepted! You can get it to me, Hayes High School or the Willis Education Center.
